<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="276" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1840,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1840,1867]" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Apterous male (
<taxonomicName box="[462,577,1842,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apterus">
<emphasis box="[462,577,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">E. apterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); male fore tibia without tympana (
<taxonomicName box="[979,1094,1842,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apterus">
<emphasis box="[979,1094,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">E. apterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); phallic sclerite (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">using terminology from</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Desutter-Grandcolas, L." box="[291,589,1877,1903]" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" pagination="525 - 561" refId="ref16549" refString="Desutter-Grandcolas, L. (2003) Phylogeny and the evolution of acoustic communication in extant Ensifera (Insecta, Orthoptera). Zoologica Scripta, 32, 525 - 561 https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1463 - 6409.2003.00142. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Desutter-Grandcolas 2003</bibRefCitation>
): Pseudepiphallus short, width much greater than its length; pseudepiphallus posterolateral projections divided into pseudepiphallic dorsal branch (Ps.db) and pseudepiphallic ventral branch (A sclerite); “A” sclerite little distinguished ventrally or even tubercle (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Souza-Dias, P. G. B. &amp; Bolfarini, M. P. &amp; Nihei, S. S. &amp; de Mello, F. A. G." box="[957,1216,1949,1975]" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" pagination="120 - 130" refId="ref18117" refString="Souza-Dias, P. G. B., Bolfarini, M. P., Nihei, S. S. &amp; de Mello, F. A. G. (2014) Endecous apterus: a new species of cave cricket from northeast Brazil, with comments on the use of subterranean habitats by Luzarinae crickets (Orthoptera: Grylloidea: Phalangopsidae: Luzarinae). Zootaxa, 3784 (2), 120 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3784.2.2" type="journal article" year="2014">
Souza-Dias 
<emphasis box="[1093,1142,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 3, A–D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1840,2011]" box="[199,1436,1984,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,443,1984,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">Amended Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males with tegmina developed (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Castro-Souza &amp; Zefa &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2020" box="[810,933,1985,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="didymus">
<emphasis box="[810,933,1985,2011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">E. didymus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Castro-Souza &amp; Zefa &amp; Ferreira, 2020" authorityName="Castro-Souza &amp; Zefa &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2020" box="[988,1102,1985,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troglobius" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[988,1102,1985,2011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">troglobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1109,1171,1985,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1109,1171,1985,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) or absent (
<taxonomicName box="[1305,1420,1986,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apterus">
<emphasis box="[1305,1420,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="275">E. apterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
),
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">
fore tibia with an oval auditory tympanum at inner side (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Castro-Souza &amp; Zefa &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2020" box="[792,916,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="didymus">
<emphasis box="[792,916,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">E. didymus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Castro-Souza &amp; Zefa &amp; Ferreira, 2020" authorityName="Castro-Souza &amp; Zefa &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2020" box="[972,1086,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troglobius" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[972,1086,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">troglobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1094,1157,153,179]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1094,1157,153,179]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) or without tympana (
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apterous">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">E. apterous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); phallic sclerite: as initially described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[725,922,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" pagination="7 - 88" refId="ref17038" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2014) Classification of the Phalangopsinae subfamily group, and new taxa from the subfamilies Phalangopsinae and Phaloriinae (Orthoptera: Gryllidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 23 (1), 7 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / zsr / 2014.23.1.7" type="journal article" year="2014">Gorochov (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
